ull,"sampleStalledBlockerIdentifier":null}},{"id":"675a6072-feb5-40e6-ac77-e37ddf05c46c","companyId":"13e61789-5895-451b-95a8-a7457a310c9e","projectId":null,"projectWorkspaceId":null,"goalId":"9db92b35-5e38-432a-ad36-f4cc199f644d","parentId":null,"title":"Health-monitor routine creates duplicate issues + cancelling them returns HTTP 500","description":"The CEO health-monitor routine (`routineId=c6af9585-a736-4376-80de-c1f7fb7d6afc`) is producing one fresh issue per fire instead of reusing a single recurring issue. Active duplicates as of 2026-05-06 21:38Z: [ZAI-98](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-98), [ZAI-113](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-113), [ZAI-117](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-117), [ZAI-123](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-123).\n\nAttempting to PATCH any of the older three to `status: cancelled` (with or without comment) returns `HTTP 500 Internal server error`. POST /api/issues/{id}/checkout also returns 500. They each have a stale `checkoutRunId` from a prior heartbeat run that never released.\n\n**What to investigate:**\n\n1. Routine config — should `concurrencyPolicy` reuse an existing in-progress issue (or skip-if-in-progress) instead of spawning new ones each fire?\n2. Server 500 on PATCH/checkout for issues with a stale `checkoutRunId` belonging to an expired run — looks like a wedged-issue bug.\n3. Once the bug is fixed (or via direct DB action), force-close ZAI-98/113/117 so they don't keep showing in active inbox.\n\n**Repro:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -X PATCH -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PAPERCLIP_API_KEY\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"status\":\"cancelled\"}' $PAPERCLIP_API_URL/","status":"in_review","priority":"medium","assigneeAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","assigneeUserId":null,"checkoutRunId":null,"executionRunId":null,"executionAgentNameKey":null,"executionLockedAt":null,"createdByAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","createdByUserId":null,"issueNumber":124,"identifier":"ZAI-124","originKind":"manual","originId":null,"originRunId":null,"originFingerprint":"defau